      "narrative": "TrustDB's Protocol/API is architecturally novel but partially implemented. The semantic foundation is now built and tested (51 tests): View<T> three-state returns eliminate the 'I don't know vs it doesn't exist' ambiguity that plagues every traditional database. EBP (Epistemic Bridge Protocol) enforces write-side governance at the storage boundary \u2014 agents cannot accidentally commit speculation as fact. SyncEnvelope/SyncDelta provide a universal exchange unit for mesh gossip, cross-device sync, and federation. GovernanceArtifact makes every query produce a self-contained compliance record with Blake3 integrity. What's missing: the Lens query engine (composition, compilation, execution), the wire protocol (gRPC, Arrow Flight), streaming subscriptions, and external access. The Lens API is designed to be programmatic (for AI agents) rather than string-based (SQL/Cypher) \u2014 this is intentional and architecturally correct for the machine-native market, but means no existing tooling can connect until the wire protocol ships.",
